      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — nominal completion",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (coarse 1.2M, medium 4.7M, fine 11.3M cells) were evaluated at the 5000 RPM / 5 L/min operating point. GCI values for velocity magnitude and wall shear stress were below 2.1%. All three runs completed without solver interruption. Residuals converged to 1e-5 within 3000 iterations. No numerical anomalies were flagged during post-processing.",
      "outcome": "passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-experimental-rh",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental RH index comparison — nominal completion",
      "description": "Predicted relative hemolysis index values were compared against in-vitro measurements across all 5 flow-speed combinations. RH predictions fell within ±15% of experimental means for 4 of 5 conditions; the fifth condition (3000 RPM / 3 L/min) showed 18% deviation, attributed to inlet boundary condition uncertainty. All simulation runs completed nominally. A single solver restart was required at the 6000 RPM condition due to initial divergence in the first 50 iterations; after adjusting the under-relaxation factor for pressure to 0.6 the run completed without further issue. No NaN propagation checks, no race-condition stress testing of the parallel decomposition, and no edge-case flow-reversal scenarios were exercised.",
      "outcome": "passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-sensitivity-analysis",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Geometric sensitivity sweep — nominal completion",
      "description": "Seven geometric variants (impeller tip clearance ±50 µm, volute width ±100 µm, inlet diameter ±0.5 mm) were simulated to map hemolysis sensitivity. All 21 variant runs completed with nominal solver convergence. RH rankings were stable across variants, confirming worst-case identification at nominal clearance with maximum speed. Post-processing Python scripts executed without exception across all cases; no testing of floating-point edge cases (e.g., zero-flow stall, near-zero shear rate inputs to the power-law hemolysis model) was performed.",
      "outcome": "passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-code-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
